{"id":1168,"date":"2014-07-19T16:49:18","date_gmt":"2014-07-19T15:49:18","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/ah-sp.com\/?p=1168"},"modified":"2024-07-04T03:29:15","modified_gmt":"2024-07-04T03:29:15","slug":"hadith-on-the-islamic-understanding-of-thunder","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/hadith-on-the-islamic-understanding-of-thunder\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on the Islamic Understanding of Thunder"},"content":{"rendered":"<div style=\"display:flex; gap:10px;justify-content:flex-start\" class=\"wps-pgfw-pdf-generate-icon__wrapper-frontend\">\n\t\t<a  href=\"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1168?action=genpdf&amp;id=1168\" class=\"pgfw-single-pdf-download-button\" target=_blank><img src=\"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/04\/free-pdf-download-icon-2617-thumb.png\" title=\"Generate PDF\" style=\"width:auto; height:45px;\"><\/a>\n\t\t<\/div><p>Bismillahi Wal Hamdullillah Was Salaatu Was Salaamu &#8216;Alaa Rasoolillahi<\/p>\n<p>Ammaa Ba&#8217;d:<\/p>\n<p>Imaam At tirmidhi mentions his chain of narration going back to Ibn Abaas &#8211; Radhiyallahu &#8216;Anhumaa&nbsp;who said: &#8221; The Jews came to the Messenger of Allah and they said &#8220;<em>Oh Abal Qaassim! Inform us about thunder what is it?<\/em> He replied:<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;<em><strong>An Angel from the angels who is responsible for the clouds, he has with him bolts of fire that he drives the clouds with wherever he wills<\/strong><\/em>&#8221; so they said: &#8220;<em>So what is this noise we hear (i.e. thunder<\/em>)? He replied: &#8220;<strong><em>It is him rebuking them as he drives them, so as to cause them to arrive at the goal he intends (for them)<\/em><\/strong>&#8221; (in a variant version it mentions that his response was: &#8220;<em><strong>It is his voice<\/strong><\/em>&#8220;) so they responded: &#8220;You have spoken the truth!..&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>(Collected by Imaamut Tirmidhi in his &#8216;Sunan&#8217; and declared Saheeh&#8217; in &#8216;Saheeh Sunanit Tirmidhi (2492))<\/p>\n\n\n<p> @abuhakeembilal <\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Ever wondered about the Islamic perspective on thunder? This article explores a Hadith narrated by Ibn Abbas, revealing the Prophet&#8217;s (\ufdfa) explanation of thunder&#8217;s origin and purpose. Discover the role of angels and the purpose behind the booming sound.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8867,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[13],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-1168","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-miscellaneous"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/07\/Hadith-on-the-Islamic-Understanding-of-Thunder.jpg","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1168","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1168"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1168\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/8867"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/abuhakeem.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1168"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category",